This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as diacritization, lemmatization, and morphological tagging, which are typically studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to jointly model these tasks, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with Arabic language processing, which is a specific area of interest in natural language processing and could fall under the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
